==English==

===Interjection===
'''howay'''

# (''[[Geordie]]'') General cry for [[encourage]]ment.

====Usage notes====
Term widely used in [[Geordie]] dialect of [[English]] and has much the same usage as the terms "come on" and can also be used in place of "come along".

Usage: ''"Howay the lads"'' or ''"Howay man ye slowin' wi doon like!"''

